File: internal/client/app/bootstrap.go
Package: app
Role: Composition Root
Purpose: Orchestrates client application initialization, configuration loading, local SQLite pool allocation, and automatic schema migration execution.

Functions:
func Bootstrap(ctx context.Context, v *viper.Viper) (context.Context, *App, error). Purpose: sequence flow. Invokes config loaders, opens SQLite via sqlite.Open, runs migrations via sqlite.Migrate, binds dependency container via WithApp. Errors: wrapped config, initialization, or migration schema failures.
func Shutdown(application *App) error. Purpose: lifecycle finalizer. Gracefully closes active SQLite database descriptors. Safe against nil application context or uninitialized pool targets.

***

File: internal/client/app/runtime.go
Package: app
Role: Dependency Container
Purpose: Encapsulates active runtime application state, configuration sections, and transactional resources inside type-safe context boundaries.

Types and Interfaces:
App struct. Holds immutable Config configuration model and mutable DB connection pool.
contextKey string unexported alias type mapping appContextKey constant target.

Functions:
func NewApp(cfg config.Config, db *sql.DB) *App. Standard baseline constructor.
func WithApp(ctx context.Context, application *App) context.Context. Injects active container instance into context layout.
func AppFromContext(ctx context.Context) (*App, error). Purpose: runtime resolution helper extracting active application domain. Errors: explicit error returned if container missing.
